        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 28 at 6:21PM EDT by NWS Wilmington OH</headline>
        <description>At 621 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was located over Ohio City,
moving south at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 45 mph and very heavy rain.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Visibility will be poor and hydroplaning
is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Rockford, Wabash, Mendon, Chattanooga, Neptune, Kossuth, State Route
116 at State Route 197, and Tama.

If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a sturdy building.

Motorists should slow down and use extra caution.

To report hazardous weather conditions, go to our website at
weather.gov/iln and submit your report via social media, when you can
do so safely.
</description>
